      • canada_uncompress

        public static int canada_uncompress(byte[] b,
                                    int[] y,
                                    int n,
                                    int m,
                                    int v0)
                             throws CanadaException
        Uncompresses time series data according to the Canadian algorithm.
        Parameters:
        b - is the array of compressed data bytes
        y - is the array of 4-byte uncompressed integer samples
        n - is the number of bytes in b
        m - is the number of samples (must be divisible by 4) - hydroacoustic does 10 samples of this is LEV and LEA so allow that
        v0 - is the last value, which may be freely disregarded.
        Returns:
        status code CANCOMP_SUCCESS=0, other conditions now throw an exception
        Throws:
        CanadaException - If found CANCOMP_NOT_20, or CANCOMP_CORRUPT, or CANCOMP_EXCEED note that there are m samples, but m+1 elements in array y. the last element is needed for the differences. sets *n to number of bytes used and elements of y

        compress data into a byte buffer from data
        Parameters:
        b - The ByteBuffer being used to compress the data
        data - The data samples as int[].
        m - The number of samples (must be divisible by 20)
        v0 - is used as the last value
        Returns:
        The revised number of bytes used in b
